First 5 to 7 mins of the film, there is an obstruction in the way of the camera, film starts off with a double edge and out of focus slighly, like its recording a 3D film, but then switches to just slightly out of focus, bit bright in some area's yet dark in others, towards the end of the films climax, it switches to heavily out of focus so you miss the details in the climax 

Unless you REALLY must see this film, id avoid as the film is ruined by the out of focus shots at the end. thanks for the up though and thanks for the effort.

First 5 mins of the movie you have some thing in the way of the cam, its then doubled edged from a 3d source, going onto being a bit out of focus (blurry), its too light in some places and too dark in others, to wards the films climax, it switches back to out of focus so you miss a lot of the detail of the final fight scene.

Audio is ok for the most part, slight echo, but at least its got some base to it. 

If you really must see this film, its worth a watch, other wise id wait for a better copy to be released.
